org.grouplens.lenskit.vectors

Class VectorEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.grouplens.lenskit.vectors.VectorEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public final class VectorEntry
extends Object
implements Cloneable

    An entry in a sparse vector. This represents the key-value pair at one entry in a sparse vector, similar to Map.Entry does for maps.

    The entry class does not support a public setValue method; to set the value at an entry on a mutable sparse vector, use MutableSparseVector.set(VectorEntry, double). This design allows the same VectorEntry to work for both Mutable and Immutable vectors, since the Immutable vectors can safely return the VectorEntry knowing it cannot change the (immutable) values, while the set operation on Mutable vectors allows the element to be changed.

    Since:
    0.11
